caption_original: Join us Wednesday October 12th, at 10 am PDT (1 pm EDT) for a Facebook Live event hosted by Dr. Joyce Boye, the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations’ Special Ambassador for the International Year of Pulses 2016! An internationally acclaimed scientist, Dr. Boye is the Director of Research, Development and Technology, at Agriculture Canada’s Agassiz and Summerland Research and Development Centres. Dr. Boye will be delivering a 30 minute presentation touching on the importance of the International Year of Pulses and her role as ambassador, as well as the benefits of pulses, and the many products that can be derived from this highly diverse crop. Have your questions ready, as Dr. Boye will also be answering questions received in the comments during the event.
